name: Wide Lens
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It’s a magnifying lens\nthat slightly boosts the accuracy of the holder’s moves.

name: Muscle Band
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This headband\nexudes strength, slightly boosting the power of the\nholder’s physical moves.

name: Wise Glasses
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This thick pair of\nglasses slightly boosts the power of the holder’s\nspecial moves.

name: Expert Belt
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It’s a well-worn\nbelt that slightly boosts the power of the holder’s\nsupereffective moves.

name: Light Clay
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder\nuses protective moves like Light Screen or Reflect,\ntheir effects will last longer than usual.

name: Life Orb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It boosts the power\nof the holder’s moves, but the holder also loses a small\namount of HP with each attack it lands.

name: Power Herb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It allows the holder\nto immediately use a move that normally requires a turn\nto charge—but only once.

name: Toxic Orb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It’s a bizarre orb that\nexudes toxins when touched and will badly poison the\nholder during battle.

name: Flame Orb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It’s a bizarre orb that\ngives off heat when touched and will afflict the holder\nwith a burn during battle.

name: Quick Powder
description: An item to be held by Ditto. Extremely fine yet hard,\nthis odd powder boosts Ditto’s Speed stat.

name: Focus Sash
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder has full\nHP and it is hit with a move that should knock it out,\nit will endure with 1 HP—but only once.

name: Zoom Lens
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder acts\nafter its target, its move will be more accurate than usual.

name: Metronome
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It boosts the power\nof a move that’s used repeatedly. Once the chain is\nbroken, the move’s power returns to normal.

name: Iron Ball
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It lowers the holder’s\nSpeed stat and makes the holder vulnerable to Ground-\ntype moves even if it is a Flying type or is levitating.

name: Lagging Tail
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. A tail of something,\nthis item is tremendously heavy and makes the holder\nmove slower than usual.

name: Destiny Knot
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. Should the holder of\nthis bright-red thread become infatuated, the Pokémon\nit is infatuated with will be similarly afflicted.

name: Black Sludge
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder is a\nPoison type, this sludge will gradually restore its HP.\nIt damages any other type.

name: Icy Rock
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder\nchanges the weather to snow, the snow will persist for\nlonger than usual.

name: Smooth Rock
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder\nchanges the weather to a sandstorm, the storm will\npersist for longer than usual.

name: Heat Rock

name: Damp Rock
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder\nchanges the weather to rain, the rain will persist for\nlonger than usual.

name: Grip Claw
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. When the holder uses\nmoves that deal damage over several turns, such as\nBind or Wrap, their effects will last longer than usual.

name: Choice Scarf
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This curious scarf\nboosts the holder’s Speed stat but only allows the use of\na single move.

name: Sticky Barb

name: Power Bracer
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. Holding this bracer\nreduces a Pokémon’s Speed in battle but allows its\nAttack stat to grow more quickly.

name: Power Belt

name: Power Lens

name: Power Band
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. Holding this band\nreduces a Pokémon’s Speed in battle but allows its\nSp. Def stat to grow more quickly.

name: Power Anklet

name: Power Weight

name: Shed Shell

name: Big Root

description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This stone tablet is\nimbued with the essence of dragons and boosts the\npower of the holder’s Dragon-type moves.

name: Dread Plate
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This stone tablet is\nimbued with the essence of darkness and boosts the\npower of the holder’s Dark-type moves.

name: Iron Plate
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This stone tablet is\nimbued with the essence of steel and boosts the power\nof the holder’s Steel-type moves.

name: Odd Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This incense has\na curious aroma that boosts the power of the holder’s\nPsychic-type moves.

name: Rock Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This incense has\na curious aroma that boosts the power of the holder’s\nRock-type moves.

name: Full Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This incense has\na curious aroma that makes the holder move slower\nthan usual.

name: Wave Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This incense has\na curious aroma that boosts the power of the holder’s\nWater-type moves.

name: Rose Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This incense has\na curious aroma that boosts the power of the holder’s\nGrass-type moves.

name: Luck Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It doubles any prize\nmoney received as long as the holder joins the battle at\nleast once.

name: Pure Incense
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It helps keep wild\nPokémon away when the holder is the head of the party.

name: Protector
description: A protective item of some sort. It is extremely stiff\nand heavy. It’s loved by a certain Pokémon.

name: Electirizer
description: A box packed with a tremendous amount of electric\nenergy. It’s loved by a certain Pokémon.

name: Magmarizer
description: A box packed with a tremendous amount of magma\nenergy. It’s loved by a certain Pokémon.

name: Dubious Disc
description: A transparent device overflowing with dubious data.\nIt’s loved by a certain Pokémon.

name: Reaper Cloth
description: A cloth imbued with horrifyingly strong spiritual energy.\nIt’s loved by a certain Pokémon.

name: Razor Claw
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This sharply hooked\nclaw boosts the critical-hit ratio of the holder’s moves.

name: Razor Fang
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This sharply hooked\nfang may cause the target to flinch whenever the holder\nsuccessfully inflicts damage on them with an attack.

name: Explorer Kit
description: A bag filled with convenient tools for exploring.\nIt provides access to the Underground in the\nSinnoh region.

name: Loot Sack
description: A sturdy, spacious bag that is used to carry any\ntreasures or loot obtained in the coal mine.

name: Rule Book
description: It lists the rules for holding battles.\nFor Link Battles, you may choose which set of rules\nyou wish to use.

name: Poké Radar
description: A tool that can search out Pokémon that are hiding\nin the tall grass. Its battery is recharged as you walk.

name: Point Card
description: A card that lists how many Battle Points you\nhave earned.

name: Guidebook
description: A notebook that keeps a record of your adventure so far.

name: Sticker Case
description: A case for storing Stickers that can be applied to\nBall Capsules.

name: Fashion Case
description: A wondrous, pretty case to store lots of colorful Props\nfor your Pokémon to wear in a musical.

name: Sticker Bag
description: A tiny bag that can hold 10 Stickers for decorating\nBall Capsules.

name: Pal Pad
description: A convenient notepad that is used to register your\nfriends and keep a record of your gameplay.

name: Works Key
description: A large key for operating the doors of the Valley\nWindworks in the canyon. It was held by a Team\nGalactic Grunt.

name: Old Charm
description: An ancient good-luck charm made of Pokémon\nbones to be taken to the elder of Celestic Town.

name: Galactic Key
description: A card key for disengaging the security systems in the\nGalactic HQ. Losing it can result in punishment,\napparently.

name: Red Chain
description: A mythical chain that is said to bind the Legendary\nPokémon that created the Sinnoh region.

name: Town Map
description: A very convenient map that can be viewed anytime.\nIt even shows you your present location in the region.

name: Vs. Seeker
description: A device that indicates Trainers who want to battle.\nIts battery charges while you walk.

name: Coin Case
description: A case for holding coins obtained at the Game Corner.\nIt can hold up to 50,000 coins.

name: Old Rod
description: An old and beat-up fishing rod. Use it at bodies of water\nto fish for Pokémon.

name: Good Rod
description: A new, good-quality fishing rod. Use it at bodies of\nwater to fish for Pokémon.

name: Super Rod
description: An awesome, high-spec fishing rod. Use it at bodies of\nwater to fish for Pokémon.

name: Sprayduck
description: A watering can shaped like a Psyduck. It helps promote\nthe healthy growth of any Berries planted in good, soft\nsoil.

name: Poffin Case
description: A case for storing Poffins cooked from Berries.

name: Bike
description: A folding bike that enables a rider to get around\nmuch faster than with Running Shoes.

name: Suite Key
description: A key to one of the suites at a certain luxury hotel\nby a lake. For some odd reason, it often disappears.

name: Oak’s Letter
description: A letter from Professor Oak. Written in it is a request for\nyou to go to Route 224.

name: Lunar Feather
description: A feather that glows like the moon. It’s said to possess\nthe power to dispel nightmares.

name: Member Card
description: A card needed for entering the inn in Canalave City.\nOddly, the last date marked on it was 50 years ago.

name: Azure Flute
description: A flute that puts out echoing sounds that do not seem\nto be of this world. No one knows who made it or when.

name: S.S. Ticket
description: A ticket required for sailing on the high-speed ferry\nS.S. Aqua. It has a drawing of a ship on it.

name: Contest Pass
description: A pass required for entering Pokémon Contests.\nIt has a drawing of an award ribbon on its front.

name: Magma Stone
description: A stone formed by boulders melting in intensely hot\nmagma, then hardening. Magma remains sealed inside it.

name: Parcel
description: A parcel entrusted into your care. You’re supposed to\ndeliver it to your childhood friend who left Twinleaf Town.

name: Coupon 1
description: A coupon to be exchanged for a Pokémon Watch—\nPokétch for short. Three coupons are needed.

name: Coupon 2
description: A coupon to be exchanged for a Pokémon Watch—\nPokétch for short. Three coupons are needed.

name: Coupon 3
description: A coupon to be exchanged for a Pokémon Watch—\nPokétch for short. Three coupons are needed.

name: Storage Key
description: The key to Team Galactic’s sinister warehouse located at\nthe edge of Veilstone City.

name: Secret Medicine
description: A fantastic medicine dispensed by the pharmacy in\nCianwood City. It fully heals a Pokémon of any ailment.

name: Vs. Recorder
description: An amazing device that can record a battle between\nfriends or the battles at certain special battle facilities.

name: Gracidea
description: A flower sometimes bundled into a bouquet to be given\nas an expression of gratitude on special occasions,\nsuch as birthdays and anniversaries.

name: Secret Key
description: A high-tech key that has to be used at a specific\nlocation. It emits a special electronic signal to open\na door.

name: Apricorn Box
description: A handy box where you can store up to 99 of each\nkind of Apricorn.

name: Unown Report
description: A report of all the discovered kinds of Unown.

name: Berry Pots
description: Portable containers that allow you to easily cultivate\nBerries anywhere and anytime.

name: Dowsing Machine
description: The latest device for showing the location of hidden\nitems. It’s worn on the head when in use.

name: Blue Card
description: A card to save points for the Buena’s Password show.

name: Slowpoke Tail
description: A very tasty tail of something. It can be sold at a high\nprice to shops.

name: Clear Bell
description: A very old-fashioned bell that makes a gentle\nringing sound.

name: Card Key
description: A card key that opens a shutter in the Radio Tower.

name: Basement Key
description: A key that opens a door in the Goldenrod Tunnel.

name: Squirt Bottle
description: A bottle used for watering plants in the Berry Pots.

name: Red Scale
description: A scale from a red Gyarados that appeared at the Lake\nof Rage. It glows red like a flame.

name: Lost Item
description: The Mime Jr. doll that was lost by the Copycat.

name: Pass
description: A pass required for riding the Magnet Train. It allows you\nto ride whenever and however much you’d like.

name: Machine Part
description: An important part of a machine that was stolen from the\nPower Plant.

name: Silver Feather
description: A strange feather that gleams with a silvery color.

name: Rainbow Feather
description: A strange feather that gleams in rainbow colors.

name: Mystery Egg
description: An Egg obtained from Mr. Pokémon. It has a mysterious\npattern on it, and what is in the Egg is unknown.

name: Red Apricorn
description: A red Apricorn. It has a pungent scent that assails\nthe nostrils.

name: Blue Apricorn
description: A blue Apricorn. It has a slightly grassy smell to it.

name: Yellow Apricorn
description: A yellow Apricorn. It has a light, refreshing scent.

name: Green Apricorn
description: A green Apricorn. It has a mysterious and aromatic scent.

name: Pink Apricorn
description: A pink Apricorn. It has a pleasantly sweet scent.

name: White Apricorn
description: A white Apricorn. It doesn’t have any aroma at all.

name: Black Apricorn
description: A black Apricorn. It has a smell that cannot be captured\nin words.

name: Fast Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is more effective\nwhen catching Pokémon that are usually very quick to\nrun away.

name: Level Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that becomes more\neffective the lower the level of the Pokémon compared\nto your own Pokémon.

name: Lure Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is more effective\nwhen catching Pokémon in or on the water.

name: Heavy Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that becomes more\neffective the heavier the Pokémon is.

name: Love Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is more effective\nwhen catching Pokémon of the opposite gender to your\nown Pokémon.

name: Friend Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that makes a wild\nPokémon more friendly toward you immediately after\nit’s caught.

name: Moon Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is more effective\nwhen catching Pokémon that can be evolved using a\nMoon Stone.

name: Sport Ball
description: A special Poké Ball that was used during the\nBug-Catching Contest in the Johto region.

name: Park Ball
description: A special Poké Ball used in the Pal Park.

name: Photo Album
description: A nice photo album for storing all the photos taken\nalong your adventure.

name: GB Sounds
description: A music player that allows you to listen to nostalgic\nsongs. It’s operated with the flip of a single switch.

name: Tidal Bell
description: A very old-fashioned bell that makes a gentle\nringing sound.

name: Rage Candy Bar
description: Mahogany Town’s famous candy. It can be used to\ncure any status condition a Pokémon may have.

name: Data Card 01
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany victories you have had in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 02
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany losses you have had in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 03
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon dashed in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 04
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon jumped in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 05
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Hurdle Dash.

name: Data Card 06
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Relay Run.

name: Data Card 07
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Pennant Capture.

name: Data Card 08
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Block Smash.

name: Data Card 09
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Disc Catch.

name: Data Card 10
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Snow Throw.

name: Data Card 11
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany points your Pokémon scored in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 12
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon failed in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 13
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon impeded themselves.

name: Data Card 14
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon tackled in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 15
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon fell down in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 16
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Ring Drop.

name: Data Card 17
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Lamp Jump.

name: Data Card 18
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Circle Push.

name: Data Card 19
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany Link Pokéathlon wins you have had.

name: Data Card 20
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany Link Pokéathlon losses you have had.

name: Data Card 21
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you have won a Pokéathlon event.

name: Data Card 22
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you have lost a Pokéathlon event.

name: Data Card 23
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you switched Pokémon in the Pokéathlon.

name: Data Card 24
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you won the Pokéathlon’s Goal Roll.

name: Data Card 25
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times your Pokémon won individual prizes.

name: Data Card 26
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmany times you instructed your Pokémon.

name: Data Card 27
description: It holds Pokéathlon records. It is a card that shows how\nmuch time you spent participating in the Pokéathlon.

name: Jade Orb
description: A shiny green orb that is said to have a deep connection\nto a legend of the Hoenn region.

name: Lock Capsule
description: A sturdy Capsule that can only be opened with a\nspecial key.

name: Red Orb
description: A shiny red orb that is said to have a deep connection\nto a legend of the Hoenn region.

name: Blue Orb
description: A shiny blue orb that is said to have a deep connection\nto a legend of the Hoenn region.

name: Enigma Stone
description: A crystal ball that was excavated from the ground.\nIt is covered with bits of rock and earth, but it is still\nvery beautiful.

name: Prism Scale
description: A mysterious scale that causes a certain Pokémon\nto evolve. It shines in rainbow colors.

name: Eviolite
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This mysterious\nevolutionary lump boosts the Defense and Sp. Def\nstats when held by a Pokémon that can still evolve.

name: Float Stone
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This very light stone\nreduces the weight of the holder.

name: Rocky Helmet
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If another Pokémon\nmakes direct contact with the holder, that Pokémon will\nbe damaged.

name: Air Balloon
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This balloon makes\nthe holder float in the air. If the holder is hit with an\nattack, the balloon will burst.

name: Red Card
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder is\ndamaged by an attack, the mysterious power of this\ncard can remove the attacker from the battle.

name: Ring Target
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. Moves that would\nnormally have no effect due to type matchups will still\nhit the holder.

name: Binding Band
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This band boosts\nthe power of binding moves used by the holder.

name: Absorb Bulb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This single-use bulb\nboosts the Sp. Atk stat if the holder is damaged by a\nWater-type attack.

name: Cell Battery
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This single-use\nbattery boosts the Attack stat if the holder is damaged\nby an Electric-type attack.

name: Eject Button
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder is\ndamaged by an attack, it will be switched out of battle\nto be replaced by another Pokémon on your team.

name: Fire Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of fire and will boost the power of a\nFire-type move—but only once.

name: Water Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of water and will boost the power of a\nWater-type move—but only once.

name: Electric Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of electricity and will boost the power\nof an Electric-type move—but only once.

name: Grass Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of plants and will boost the power of\na Grass-type move—but only once.

name: Ice Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of ice and will boost the power of an\nIce-type move—but only once.

name: Fighting Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of the fighting spirit and will boost the\npower of a Fighting-type move—but only once.

name: Poison Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of poison and will boost the power of\na Poison-type move—but only once.

name: Ground Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of the earth and will boost the power\nof a Ground-type move—but only once.

name: Flying Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of flight and will boost the power of a\nFlying-type move—but only once.

name: Psychic Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of psychic energy and will boost the\npower of a Psychic-type move—but only once.

name: Bug Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of bugs and will boost the power of a\nBug-type move—but only once.

name: Rock Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of rock and will boost the power of a\nRock-type move—but only once.

name: Ghost Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of ghosts and will boost the power of\na Ghost-type move—but only once.

name: Dragon Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of dragons and will boost the power of\na Dragon-type move—but only once.

name: Dark Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of darkness and will boost the power\nof a Dark-type move—but only once.

name: Steel Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of steel and will boost the power of a\nSteel-type move—but only once.

name: Normal Gem
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This gem is imbued\nwith the essence of normalcy and will boost the power\nof a Normal-type move—but only once.

name: Health Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s HP stat.

name: Muscle Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s Attack stat.

name: Resist Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s Defense stat.

name: Genius Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Clever Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Swift Feather
description: An item to be used on a Pokémon. This feather slightly\nincreases base points for a Pokémon’s Speed stat.

name: Pretty Feather
description: Though this feather is beautiful, it’s just a regular feather\nand has no effect.

name: Cover Fossil
description: A fossil from a prehistoric Pokémon that once lived\nin the sea. It appears as though it could be part of a\ncreature’s back.

name: Plume Fossil
description: A fossil from a prehistoric Pokémon said to be an\nancestor to modern bird Pokémon. It looks as if it could\nhave come from part of some creature’s wing.

name: Liberty Pass
description: A special pass to go to Liberty Garden.\nBoard the ship in Castelia City.

name: Pass Orb
description: A mysterious orb containing the power of the\nUnova region, to be used when generating\nPass Power.

name: Dream Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is more effective\nwhen catching Pokémon that are asleep.

name: Poké Toy
description: A toy that attracts the attention of Pokémon.\nIt guarantees escape from any battle with wild Pokémon.

name: Prop Case
description: A wondrous, pretty case to store lots of colorful Props\nfor your Pokémon to wear in a musical.

name: Dragon Skull
description: The skull of a Pokémon that was said to have braved\nthe raging seas to fly around the world.

name: Balm Mushroom
description: A rare mushroom that gives off a nice fragrance.\nIt can be sold at a high price to shops.

name: Big Nugget
description: A big nugget of pure gold that gives off a lustrous\ngleam. It can be sold at a high price to shops.

name: Pearl String
description: Very large pearls that have a nice silvery sheen to them.\nThey can be sold at a high price to shops.

name: Comet Shard
description: A shard that fell to the ground when a comet passed\nnearby. It can be sold at a high price to shops.

name: Relic Copper
description: A copper coin used by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Relic Silver
description: A silver coin used by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Relic Gold
description: A gold coin used by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Relic Vase
description: A vase made by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Relic Band
description: A bracelet made by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Relic Statue
description: A stone figurine made by an ancient civilization\nabout three thousand years ago.

name: Relic Crown
description: A crown made by an ancient civilization about\nthree thousand years ago.

name: Casteliacone
description: Castelia City’s specialty: soft-serve ice cream. It can be\nused to cure any status condition a Pokémon may have.

name: Dire Hit 2
description: Can be used many times to boost a Pokémon’s critical-\nhit ratio. These effects disappear if the Pokémon\nleaves the battle.

name: X Speed 2
description: Sharply boosts the Speed stat of a Pokémon in\nbattle. This effect disappears if the Pokémon leaves\nthe battle.

name: X Sp. Atk 2
description: Sharply boosts the Sp. Atk stat of a Pokémon in\nbattle. This effect disappears if the Pokémon leaves\nthe battle.

name: X Sp. Def 2
description: Sharply boosts the Sp. Def stat of a Pokémon in\nbattle. This effect disappears if the Pokémon leaves\nthe battle.

name: X Defense 2
description: Sharply boosts the Defense stat of a Pokémon in\nbattle. This effect disappears if the Pokémon leaves\nthe battle.

name: X Attack 2
description: Sharply boosts the Attack stat of a Pokémon in\nbattle. This effect disappears if the Pokémon leaves\nthe battle.

name: X Accuracy 2

name: Pikanium Z

name: Decidium Z

name: Incinium Z

name: Primarium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nPrimarina’s Sparkling Aria to a Z-Move.

name: Tapunium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade the\ntapu’s Nature’s Madness to a Z-Move.

name: Marshadium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nMarshadow’s Spectral Thief to a Z-Move.

name: Aloraichium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nAlolan Raichu’s Thunderbolt to a Z-Move.

name: Snorlium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nSnorlax’s Giga Impact to a Z-Move.

name: Eevium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nEevee’s Last Resort to a Z-Move.

name: Mewnium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nMew’s Psychic to a Z-Move.

name: Pikashunium Z
description: It converts Z-Power into crystals that upgrade\nThunderbolt to a Z-Move when used by a Pikachu\nwearing a cap.

name: Pikashunium Z
description: This is a crystallized form of Z-Power.\nIt upgrades Thunderbolt to a Z-Move when used\nby a Pikachu wearing a cap.

name: Forage Bag
description: A bag to carry ingredients gathered during Mallow’s\ntrial in the jungle.

name: Fishing Rod
description: A fishing rod made by Captain Lana. Cast a line\nover piles of underwater rocks to fish for wild\naquatic Pokémon.

name: Professor’s Mask
description: The mask that belongs to The Masked Royal.\nThis pro wrestler apparently sews his mask on a\nmachine himself.

name: Festival Ticket
description: A ticket that allows you to host a mission in\nFestival Plaza.

name: Sparkling Stone
description: A stone entrusted to you by a Pokémon that has been\nvenerated as a guardian deity in the Alola region.\nThere is said to be some secret in how it sparkles.

name: Adrenaline Orb
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This orb boosts the\nSpeed stat if the holder is intimidated.

name: Zygarde Cube
description: An item in which Zygarde Cores and Cells are gathered.\nYou can also use it to change Zygarde’s forms.

name: Ice Stone
description: A peculiar stone that can make certain species of\nPokémon evolve. It has a snowflake pattern in it.

name: Ride Pager
description: By entering certain numbers on this pager,\nyou can summon Ride Pokémon in an instant.

name: Beast Ball
description: A somewhat different Poké Ball that is not very\neffective when catching Pokémon.

name: Big Malasada
description: The Alola region’s famous fried confection. It can be\nused to cure any status condition a Pokémon may have.

name: Red Nectar
description: Flower nectar obtained from a red flower. It changes the\nform of a certain species of Pokémon.

name: Yellow Nectar
description: Flower nectar obtained from a yellow flower. It changes\nthe form of a certain species of Pokémon.

name: Pink Nectar
description: Flower nectar obtained from a pink flower. It changes\nthe form of a certain species of Pokémon.

name: Purple Nectar
description: Flower nectar obtained from a purple flower. It changes\nthe form of a certain species of Pokémon.

name: Sun Flute
description: It is said that the tones it produces were offered\nup as an expression of gratitude to the Legendary\nPokémon of the sun.

name: Moon Flute
description: It is said that the tones it produces were offered\nup as an expression of gratitude to the Legendary\nPokémon of the moon.

name: Enigmatic Card
description: A mysterious card. Written on it is a request that you go\nto a guest room in the motel on Akala Island’s Route 8.

name: Silver Razz Berry
description: A Berry that makes it easier to catch Pokémon when\ngiven to them.

name: Golden Razz Berry
description: A Berry that makes it drastically easier to catch Pokémon\nwhen given to them.

name: Silver Nanab Berry
description: A Berry that calms Pokémon you’re trying to catch\nwhen given to them.

name: Golden Nanab Berry
description: A Berry that drastically calms Pokémon you’re trying\nto catch when given to them.

name: Silver Pinap Berry
description: A Berry that makes you more likely to get an item when\ngiven to Pokémon you’re trying to catch.

name: Golden Pinap Berry
description: A Berry that makes you drastically more likely to get\nan item when given to Pokémon you’re trying to catch.

name: Secret Key
description: The key that unlocks the front door of\nthe Pokémon Gym on Cinnabar Island.\nIt has a red decoration.

name: S.S. Ticket
description: The ticket required to board the S.S. Anne.\nIt has a drawing of a ship on it.

name: Silph Scope
description: A scope that lets you see what cannot usually be seen.\nIt is made by Silph Co.

name: Parcel
description: A parcel you were asked to deliver to Professor Oak\nfrom Viridian City’s Poké Mart.

name: Card Key
description: A card key that unlocks doors in Silph Co.’s head\noffice in Saffron City.

name: Gold Teeth
description: A set of golden false teeth lost by the Safari Zone’s\nwarden. They make his smile sparkle.

name: Lift Key
description: A key that operates the elevator in the Team Rocket\nHideout. It bears the Team Rocket logo.

name: Terrain Extender
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. It extends the\nduration of terrain caused by the holder’s move\nor Ability.

name: Protective Pads
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. These pads protect\nthe holder from effects triggered by making direct\ncontact with another Pokémon.

name: Electric Seed
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the terrain becomes\nElectric Terrain, the holder will use this seed to boost its\nown Defense stat.

name: Psychic Seed
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the terrain becomes\nPsychic Terrain, the holder will use this seed to boost its\nown Sp. Def stat.

name: Misty Seed
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the terrain becomes\nMisty Terrain, the holder will use this seed to boost its\nown Sp. Def stat.

name: Grassy Seed
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the terrain becomes\nGrassy Terrain, the holder will use this seed to boost its\nown Defense stat.

name: Stretchy Spring
description: A thin small spring. It’s totally stretched out, and\nwhat it’s used for is unknown.

name: Chalky Stone
description: A small whitish stone picked up at the edge of the road.

name: Marble
description: A round glass marble. You can see colored glass\ninside the transparent marble.

name: Lone Earring
description: A single earring that somebody dropped.

name: Beach Glass
description: A piece of colored glass. Waves have rounded its edges.\nIt’s slightly rough to the touch.

name: Gold Leaf
description: A mysterious gold leaf. No trees with this leaf have\nbeen found yet.

name: Silver Leaf
description: A mysterious silver leaf. No trees with this leaf have\nbeen found yet.

name: Polished Mud Ball
description: A ball made of mud. It had been polished for such\na long time that the surface is very shiny.

name: Tropical Shell
description: A beautiful white shell that may have drifted from\na sea in a warm region.

name: Leaf Letter
description: A letter written on a leaf. Something is written using\nPikachu’s footprints.

name: Leaf Letter
description: A letter written on a leaf. Something is written using\nEevee’s footprints.

name: Small Bouquet
description: A small bouquet that was made with heart and soul\nfor a single Trainer.

name: Lure
description: A bottle of perfume that makes rare Pokémon more\nlikely to appear for a short time when sprayed about.

name: Super Lure
description: A bottle of perfume that makes rare Pokémon more\nlikely to appear when sprayed about. Its effect lasts\nlonger than that of a Lure.

name: Max Lure
description: A bottle of perfume that makes rare Pokémon more\nlikely to appear when sprayed about. Its effect lasts\nlonger than that of a Super Lure.

name: Pewter Crunchies
description: Pewter City’s famous crunchy snack. They can be used\nto cure any status condition a Pokémon may have.

name: Fighting Memory

name: Lunalium Z
description: This is a crystallized form of Z-Power.\nIt upgrades Lunala’s Moongeist Beam to a Z-Move.

name: Ultranecrozium Z

name: Mimikium Z

name: Lycanium Z

name: Kommonium Z

name: Lunalium Z

name: Ultranecrozium Z

name: Z-Power Ring
description: A mysterious ring that enables Pokémon to use\nZ-Power. It requires both the willpower and the\nphysical power of the Trainer wearing it.

name: Pink Petal
description: A pressed flower petal you receive from Mina\nduring Mina’s trial. The goal is to collect seven\ndifferent kinds of petals.

name: Orange Petal
description: A pressed flower petal you receive from Ilima\nduring Mina’s trial. The goal is to collect seven\ndifferent kinds of petals.

name: Blue Petal
description: A pressed flower petal you receive from Lana\nduring Mina’s trial. The goal is to collect seven\ndifferent kinds of petals.

name: Red Petal

name: Green Petal

name: Yellow Petal

name: Purple Petal
description: A pressed flower petal you receive from Nanu\nduring Mina’s trial. The goal is to collect seven\ndifferent kinds of petals.

name: Rainbow Flower
description: A flower made of the petals you received from\ncaptains. It’s proof that your growth has been\nrecognized by them.

name: Surge Badge
description: A novelty badge that you can receive at the\nKantonian Gym. Rumor has it that it imitates\nthe Badge of a Gym somewhere.

name: N-Solarizer
description: A machine to fuse Necrozma, which needs light,\nand Solgaleo.

name: N-Lunarizer
description: A machine to fuse Necrozma, which needs light,\nand Lunala.

name: N-Solarizer
description: A machine to separate Necrozma, which needed\nlight, from Solgaleo.

name: N-Lunarizer
description: A machine to separate Necrozma, which needed\nlight, from Lunala.

name: Ilima’s Normalium Z
description: The Normalium Z you were entrusted with by Ilima.\nYou were asked to place it on the pedestal at\nthe back of Verdant Cavern.

name: Left Poké Ball
description: A Poké Ball containing a Pokémon that lost its Trainer.\nIt seems the Trainer hails from Ula’ula Island.

name: Roto Hatch
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it helps Eggs\nhatch faster.

name: Roto Bargain
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it reduces the\nprices of products at Poké Marts by half.

name: Roto Prize Money
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it triples the\nprize money you receive after battle.

name: Roto Exp. Points
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it slightly\nincreases the Exp. Points your Pokémon receive\nafter battle.

name: Roto Friendship
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it helps Pokémon\nin your party grow friendly quite a lot faster.

name: Roto Encounter
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it increases the\nchance of encountering high-level wild Pokémon for a\ncertain period of time.

name: Roto Stealth
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it prevents\nyou from encountering any wild Pokémon for a certain\nperiod of time.

name: Roto HP Restore
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it fully restores\nthe max HP of your battling Pokémon.

name: Roto PP Restore
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it fully restores\nthe max PP of your battling Pokémon.

name: Roto Boost
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it boosts all stats\nfor your battling Pokémon.

name: Roto Catch
description: One of the Rotom Powers. When used, it makes you far\nlikelier to succeed at catching the wild Pokémon in the\nimmediate area.

name: Endorsement
description: A letter of recommendation that you’ll need in order to\nparticipate in the Gym Challenge.

name: Pokémon Box Link
description: A device that allows you to access the Pokémon storage\nsystem. There are some places where it won’t work.

name: Wishing Star
description: A stone found in the Galar region with a mysterious power.\nIt’s said that your dreams come true if you find one.

name: Dynamax Band
description: A Wishing Star has been affixed to it. It lets out a light\nthat allows Pokémon to Dynamax when at a Power Spot.

name: Fishing Rod
description: Use it by the water to fish up various kinds of Pokémon.

name: Rotom Bike
description: This bike can be combined with the Pokémon Rotom to\nuse a turbo boost.

name: Sausages
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. These sausages should be\nboiled before eating.

name: Bob’s Food Tin
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The tinned food that Bob sells\nis curiously popular in Galar.

name: Bach’s Food Tin
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The tinned food that Bach sells\nis curiously popular in Galar.

name: Tin of Beans
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. When simmered, the beans\nsuffuse a dish with their mild flavor.

name: Bread
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. An indispensable tool for\nmopping up that extra curry left on your plate.

name: Pasta
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. These flour noodles make\nfor a surprisingly good match with curry.

name: Mixed Mushrooms
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The chewy texture of the\nmushrooms transforms any dish they’re added to.

name: Smoke-Poke Tail
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. When a Slowpoke’s tail falls off,\nit grows back quickly.

name: Large Leek
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Whether this is the kind of\nvegetable stalk that Farfetch’d like is unknown.

name: Fancy Apple
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. An apple chosen above others.\nIt has spectacular form and a brilliant sheen.

name: Brittle Bones
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The taste boiled off from the\nbones is sure to give a dish a light umami taste.

name: Pack of Potatoes
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Potatoes help mellow out a spicy\ntaste, to make a dish more mild.

name: Pungent Root
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Though carelessly picked, these\nherbs can add a fragrant accent to a dish.

name: Salad Mix
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The assortment of vegetables\nlooks quite appealing and healthy.

name: Fried Food
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. It’s been a while since it was\nfried, so it’s gotten greasy.

name: Boiled Egg
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Even just one boiled egg can\nreally enhance a dish.

name: Camping Gear
description: Everything you need to set up a tent and get cooking in\na Wild Area or at a camping spot.

name: Rusted Sword
description: It is said that a hero used this sword to halt a terrible\ndisaster in ancient times. But it’s grown rusty and worn.

name: Rusted Shield
description: It is said that a hero used this shield to halt a terrible\ndisaster in ancient times. But it’s grown rusty and worn.

name: Fossilized Bird
description: A fossil piece left behind by a prehistoric Pokémon that\nonce soared through the sky. What it looked like is\na mystery.

name: Fossilized Fish
description: A fossil piece left behind by a prehistoric Pokémon that\nonce lived in the sea. What it looked like is a mystery.

name: Fossilized Drake
description: A fossil piece left behind by a prehistoric Pokémon that\nonce roamed the land. What it looked like is a mystery.

name: Fossilized Dino
description: A fossil piece left behind by a prehistoric Pokémon that\nonce lived in the sea. What it looked like is a mystery.

name: Strawberry Sweet
description: A strawberry-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Love Sweet
description: A heart-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Berry Sweet
description: A berry-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Clover Sweet
description: A clover-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Flower Sweet
description: A flower-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Star Sweet
description: A star-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this, it spins\naround happily.

name: Ribbon Sweet
description: A ribbon-shaped sweet. When a Milcery holds this,\nit spins around happily.

name: Sweet Apple
description: A peculiar apple that can make a certain species of\nPokémon evolve. It’s exceptionally sweet.

name: Tart Apple
description: A peculiar apple that can make a certain species of\nPokémon evolve. It’s exceptionally tart.

name: Throat Spray
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder uses\na sound-based move, this throat spray will boost its\nSp. Atk stat.

name: Eject Pack
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder’s stats\nare lowered, it will be switched out of battle.

name: Heavy-Duty Boots
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. These boots protect\nthe holder from the effects of traps and the like set on\nthe battlefield.

name: Blunder Policy
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If the holder misses\nwith a move due to low accuracy, this policy will sharply\nboost its Speed stat.

name: Room Service
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. If Trick Room takes\neffect, this item will lower the holder’s Speed stat.

name: Utility Umbrella
description: An item to be held by a Pokémon. This sturdy umbrella\nprotects the holder from the effects of rain and harsh\nsunlight.

name: Exp. Candy XS
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed,\nit grants a Pokémon a very small number of Exp. Points.

name: Exp. Candy S
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed,\nit grants a Pokémon a small number of Exp. Points.

name: Exp. Candy M
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed,\nit grants a Pokémon a moderate number of Exp. Points.

name: Exp. Candy L
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed,\nit grants a Pokémon a large number of Exp. Points.

name: Exp. Candy XL
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed,\nit grants a Pokémon a very large number of Exp. Points.

name: Dynamax Candy
description: A candy that is packed with energy. If consumed, it raises\nthe Dynamax Level of a Pokémon by one. A higher level\nmeans higher HP when Dynamaxed.

name: TR00
description: A frenetic dance to uplift the fighting spirit.\nThis sharply raises the user’s Attack stat.

name: TR01
description: The user drops onto the target with its full body\nweight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: TR02
description: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire.\nThis may also leave the target with a burn.

name: TR03
description: The target is blasted by a huge volume of water\nlaunched under great pressure.

name: TR04
description: The user attacks everything around it by swamping\nits surroundings with a giant wave.

name: TR05
description: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy.\nThis may also leave the target frozen.

name: TR06
description: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing\nPokémon. This may also leave the opposing\nPokémon frozen.

name: TR07
description: A powerful low kick that makes the target fall over.\nThe heavier the target, the greater the move’s power.

name: TR08
description: A strong electric blast crashes down on the target.\nThis may also leave the target with paralysis.

name: TR09
description: A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on the target to\ninflict damage. This may also leave the target\nwith paralysis.

name: TR10
description: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every\nPokémon around it.

name: TR11
description: The target is hit by a strong telekinetic force.\nThis may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: TR12
description: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move\nfaster. This sharply raises the Speed stat.

name: TR13
description: The user takes a deep breath and focuses so that\ncritical hits land more easily.

name: TR14
description: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain\ninto randomly using nearly any move.

name: TR15
description: The target is attacked with an intense blast of\nall-consuming fire. This may also leave the target\nwith a burn.

name: TR16
description: The user charges at the target and may make\nit flinch.

name: TR17
description: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its\nconcerns. This sharply raises the user’s Sp. Def stat.

name: TR18
description: The user drains the target’s blood. The user’s HP is\nrestored by half the damage taken by the target.

name: TR19
description: The user strikes with a simultaneous three-beam attack.\nThis may also burn, freeze, or paralyze the target.

name: TR20
description: The user creates a substitute for itself using some of\nits own HP. The substitute serves as the user’s decoy.

name: TR21
description: An all-out attack that becomes more powerful the\nless HP the user has.

name: TR22
description: Unsanitary sludge is hurled at the target. This may\nalso poison the target.

name: TR23
description: The user lays a trap of spikes at the opposing\nteam’s feet. The trap hurts Pokémon that switch\ninto battle.

name: TR24
description: The user rampages and attacks for two to three\nturns. The user then becomes confused.

name: TR25
description: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack\nthe target. This attack does physical damage.

name: TR26
description: The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP.\nIts chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: TR27
description: While it is asleep, the user randomly uses one of the\nmoves it knows.

name: TR28
description: Using its tough and impressive horn, the user rams\ninto the target with no letup.

name: TR29
description: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in\nwaiting and passes along any stat changes.

name: TR30
description: The user compels the target to keep using the move\nit encored for three turns.

name: TR31
description: The target is slammed with a steel-hard tail.\nThis may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: TR32
description: The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs.\nThis may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: TR33
description: The user hurls a shadowy blob at the target.\nThis may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: TR34
description: Two turns after this move is used, a hunk of psychic\nenergy attacks the target.

name: TR35
description: The user attacks in an uproar for three turns.\nDuring that time, no Pokémon can fall asleep.

name: TR36
description: The user attacks by exhaling hot breath on opposing\nPokémon. This may also leave those Pokémon with\na burn.

name: TR37
description: The target is taunted into a rage that allows it to use\nonly attack moves for three turns.

name: TR38
description: The user catches the target off guard and swaps its\nheld item with its own.

name: TR39
description: The user attacks the target with great power.\nHowever, this also lowers the user’s Attack and\nDefense stats.

name: TR40
description: The user employs its psychic power to exchange\nAbilities with the target.

name: TR41
description: The user launches a kick that lands a critical hit\nmore easily. This may also leave the target with\na burn.

name: TR42
description: The user lets loose a horribly echoing shout with\nthe power to inflict damage.

name: TR43
description: The user attacks the target at full power. The attack’s\nrecoil harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: TR44
description: The user absorbs a mystical power from space to\nraise its Defense and Sp. Def stats.

name: TR45
description: The user attacks by shooting muddy water at opposing\nPokémon. This may also lower their accuracy.

name: TR46
description: The user hardens its body’s surface like iron,\nsharply raising its Defense stat.

name: TR47
description: The user slashes the target with huge sharp claws.

name: TR48
description: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body,\nraising both its Attack and Defense stats.

name: TR49
description: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its\nspirit to raise its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

name: TR50
description: The user handles a sharp leaf like a sword and\nattacks by cutting its target. Critical hits land\nmore easily.

name: TR51
description: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful\ndance that raises its Attack and Speed stats.

name: TR52
description: The user tackles the target with a high-speed spin.\nThe slower the user compared to the target, the\ngreater the move’s power.

name: TR53
description: The user fights the target up close without guarding\nitself. This also lowers the user’s Defense and\nSp. Def stats.

name: TR54
description: The user lays a trap of poison spikes at the feet of\nthe opposing team. The spikes will poison opposing\nPokémon that switch into battle.

name: TR55
description: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges the target.\nThis also damages the user quite a lot. This attack\nmay leave the target with a burn.

name: TR56
description: The user lets loose a blast of aura power from deep\nwithin its body at the target. This attack\nnever misses.

name: TR57
description: The target is stabbed with a tentacle, arm, or the like\nsteeped in poison. This may also poison the target.

name: TR58
description: The user releases a horrible aura imbued with dark\nthoughts. This may also make the target flinch.

name: TR59
description: The user slams a barrage of hard-shelled seeds\ndown on the target from above.

name: TR60
description: The user slashes at the target by crossing its\nscythes or claws as if they were a pair of scissors.

name: TR61
description: The user generates a damaging sound wave by\nvibration. This may also lower the target’s\nSp. Def stat.

name: TR62
description: The target is attacked with a shock wave generated\nby the user’s gaping mouth.

name: TR63
description: The user attacks with a ray of light that sparkles as\nif it were made of gemstones.

name: TR64
description: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes\nits power. This may also lower the target’s\nSp. Def stat.

name: TR65
description: The user draws power from nature and fires it at the\ntarget. This may also lower the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: TR66
description: The user tucks in its wings and charges from a low\naltitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.

name: TR67
description: The user makes the ground under the target erupt\nwith power. This may also lower the target’s\nSp. Def stat.

name: TR68
description: The user stimulates its brain by thinking bad\nthoughts. This sharply raises the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: TR69
description: The user focuses its willpower to its head and\nattacks the target. This may also make the\ntarget flinch.

name: TR70
description: The user gathers all its light energy and releases it\nall at once. This may also lower the target’s\nSp. Def stat.

name: TR71
description: The user whips up a storm of leaves around the\ntarget. The attack’s recoil harshly lowers the user’s\nSp. Atk stat.

name: TR72
description: The user violently whirls its vines, tentacles, or the\nlike to harshly lash the target.

name: TR73
description: The user shoots filthy garbage at the target to\nattack. This may also poison the target.

name: TR74
description: The user slams the target with its steel-hard head.\nThis may also make the target flinch.

name: TR75
description: The user stabs the target from below with\nsharpened stones. Critical hits land more easily.

name: TR76
description: The user lays a trap of levitating stones around the\nopposing team. The trap hurts opposing Pokémon\nthat switch into battle.

name: TR77
description: The user snares the target with grass and trips it.\nThe heavier the target, the greater the\nmove’s power.

name: TR78
description: The user strikes everything around it by swamping\nthe area with a giant sludge wave. This may also\npoison those hit.

name: TR79
description: The user slams into the target with its heavy body.\nThe more the user outweighs the target, the greater\nthe move’s power.

name: TR80
description: The user hurls an electric orb at the target. The\nfaster the user is than the target, the greater the\nmove’s power.

name: TR81
description: The user turns the target’s power against it.\nThe higher the target’s Attack stat, the greater\nthe damage it deals.

name: TR82
description: The user attacks the target with stored power.\nThe more the user’s stats are raised, the greater\nthe move’s power.

name: TR83
description: The user teleports using a strange power and\nswitches places with one of its allies.

name: TR84
description: The user shoots boiling hot water at its target.\nThis may also leave the target with a burn.

name: TR85
description: The user is roused, and its Attack and Sp. Atk\nstats increase.

name: TR86
description: The user shrouds itself in electricity and smashes\ninto its target. This also damages the user a little.

name: TR87
description: The user crashes into its target while rotating its\nbody like a drill. Critical hits land more easily.

name: TR88
description: The user slams its target with its flame-covered\nbody. The more the user outweighs the target, the\ngreater the move’s power.

name: TR89
description: The user attacks by wrapping its opponent in a\nfierce wind that flies up into the sky. This may also\nconfuse the target.

name: TR90
description: The user plays rough with the target and attacks it.\nThis may also lower the target’s Attack stat.

name: TR91
description: Opposing Pokémon are drenched in an odd\npoisonous liquid. This lowers the Attack, Sp. Atk, and\nSpeed stats of a poisoned target.

name: TR92
description: The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a\npowerful flash.

name: TR93
description: The user swings both arms and hits the target.\nThe target’s stat changes don’t affect this\nattack’s damage.

name: TR94
description: The user fiercely attacks the target using its\nentire body.

name: TR95
description: The user attacks the target’s throat, and the\nresultant suffering prevents the target from using\nmoves that emit sound for two turns.

name: TR96
description: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that\nexplodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a\npollen puff that restores its HP instead.

name: TR97
description: The user bites the target with its psychic\ncapabilities. This can also destroy Light Screen\nand Reflect.

name: TR98
description: The user slams into the target using a full-force\nblast of water. This may also lower the target’s\nDefense stat.

name: TR99
description: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target.\nThe higher the user’s Defense, the more damage it can\ninflict on the target.

name: TM00
description: The target is slugged by a punch thrown with\nmuscle-packed power.

name: Lonely Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Attack\nstat grow stronger. However, its Defense stat may suffer.

name: Adamant Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Attack\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Atk stat may suffer.

name: Naughty Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Attack\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Def stat may suffer.

name: Brave Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Attack\nstat grow stronger. However, its Speed stat may suffer.

name: Bold Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Defense\nstat grow stronger. However, its Attack stat may suffer.

name: Impish Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Defense\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Atk stat may suffer.

name: Lax Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Defense\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Def stat may suffer.

name: Relaxed Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Defense\nstat grow stronger. However, its Speed stat may suffer.

name: Modest Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Atk\nstat grow stronger. However, its Attack stat may suffer.

description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Atk\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Def stat may suffer.

description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Atk\nstat grow stronger. However, its Speed stat may suffer.

name: Calm Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Def\nstat grow stronger. However, its Attack stat may suffer.

name: Gentle Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Def\nstat grow stronger. However, its Defense stat may suffer.

name: Careful Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Def\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Atk stat may suffer.

name: Sassy Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Sp. Def\nstat grow stronger. However, its Speed stat may suffer.

name: Timid Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Speed\nstat grow stronger. However, its Attack stat may suffer.

name: Hasty Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Speed\nstat grow stronger. However, its Defense stat may suffer.

name: Jolly Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Speed\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Atk stat may suffer.

name: Naive Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint can make its Speed\nstat grow stronger. However, its Sp. Def stat may suffer.

name: Serious Mint
description: Having a Pokémon smell this mint will cause its Attack,\nDefense, Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats to grow at\nan equal rate.

name: Wishing Piece
description: Throw one into a Pokémon Den to attract\na wild Dynamax Pokémon.

name: Cracked Pot
description: A peculiar teapot that can make a certain species of\nPokémon evolve. It may be cracked, but tea poured\nfrom it is delicious.

name: Chipped Pot
description: A peculiar teapot that can make a certain species of\nPokémon evolve. It may be chipped, but tea poured\nfrom it is delicious.

name: Hi-tech Earbuds
description: Strange earbuds that allow you to freely control the\nvolume of various sounds.

name: Fruit Bunch
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The syrupy fruits give off a strong\ntropical feel.

name: Moomoo Cheese
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Melted cheese can really give a\ncurry some richness.

name: Spice Mix
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. There are over fifty spices\ncontained within this ingredient’s hot flavor.

name: Fresh Cream
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Add some whipped cream to a\nspicy curry to give it some sweetness.

name: Packaged Curry
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. Using packaged curry helps\nmake sure there are no slipups when cooking.

name: Coconut Milk
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. The refined sweetness of this\ncoconut milk makes it quite popular.

name: Instant Noodles
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. It has a junk-food sort of taste,\nbut it goes well with curry.

name: Precooked Burger
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. If you’re unsure about what to\ncook, you can’t go wrong with some burger.

name: Gigantamix
description: One of the many ingredients that can be used for\ncooking at your camp. A mysterious spice. Even a tiny\nsprinkle is sure to make a curry gigantic.

name: Wishing Chip
description: Toss a number of them into a Pokémon Den for the\nchance to attract a wild Dynamax Pokémon.

name: Rotom Bike
description: This bike can be combined with the Pokémon Rotom to\nnot only do a turbo boost but also run on the water.

name: Catching Charm
description: Having one of these mysterious, unshakable charms\nmakes it more likely you’ll get a critical catch.

name: Old Letter
description: A letter entrusted to you by a girl, to be delivered to\na boy. Strangely, it looks old to you.

name: Band Autograph
description: It’s signed by all members of the Galar region’s most\ncharismatic band, the Maximizers.

name: Sonia’s Book
description: Professor Sonia’s published writings. Her new\ndiscoveries about the Galar region’s legends are\nrecorded in this enjoyable read.

name: Rotom Catalog
description: A catalog of devices that Rotom like. Use the catalog\nto have Rotom hop in and out of the various devices\nlisted within.

name: ★And458
description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

name: ★And15
description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.

description: An item that causes [VAR 0101(0000)] to appear from\nthe Watchtower Lair in the Wild Area until the end of\nthe day.
